{"questionId":"9076253","questionHtml":"<div class=\"qb-parent-stem\"><p>The pressure–volume (<em>pV</em>) diagram shows a cycle ABCA of a heat engine. The working substance of the engine is 0.221 mol of ideal monatomic gas.</p>\n<p style=\"text-align:left;\"><img src=\"__IMG__/6a22de4844043fe6723e1e1e566a07dc6108d9c0.png\"></p>\n<p>At A the temperature of the gas is 295 K and the pressure of the gas is 1.10 × 10<sup>5</sup> Pa. The process from A to B is adiabatic.</p></div>\n<div class=\"qb-leaf-prompt\"><p>For the process BC, calculate, in J,&nbsp;the work done by the gas.</p></div>","markschemeHtml":"<p><strong>«</strong>W = <em>p</em>Δ<em>V</em><strong>»</strong></p>\n<p><strong>«</strong>= 5.07 ×&nbsp;10<sup>5</sup>&nbsp;×&nbsp;(5 ×&nbsp;10<sup>–3</sup> – 2 ×&nbsp;10<sup>–3</sup>)<strong>» </strong></p>\n<p>= 1.52 ×&nbsp;10<sup>3</sup>&nbsp;<strong>«</strong>J<strong>»</strong></p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p><em>Award </em><strong><em>[0] </em></strong><em>if POT mistake.</em></p>\n<p><strong><em>[1 mark]</em></strong></p>","meta":{"questionId":"9076253","referenceCode":"18M.3.SL.TZ1.b.i","subjectId":"46-dp-physics-last-assessment-2024","title":"For the process BC, calculate, in J, the work done by the gas.","paper":"3","level":"SL","questionNumber":"b.i","marksAvailable":"[Maximum mark: 1]","breadcrumbLabels":["Option B: Engineering physics","Option B: Engineering physics","Option B: Engineering physics (Core topics)","B.2 – Thermodynamics","Option B: Engineering physics","Option B: Engineering physics (Core topics)"],"memberSectionIds":[],"sectionOrders":{}},"schemaVersion":2}